-- Woods, Mickelson, Watson Grouped for First 2 Rounds of U.S. Open
-- B y   M i c h a e l   B u t e a u
-- 2012-06-08T04:01:56Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-08/woods-mickelson-watson-grouped-for-first-2-rounds-of-u-s-open.html
Tiger Woods ,  Phil Mickelson  and Bubba Watson will play in the same group for the first two rounds of
next week’s U.S Open, the U.S. Golf Association announced.  Woods is a three-time U.S. Open champion, while Mickelson
has five runner-up finishes in the event to go with three
Masters Tournament titles and the 2005 PGA Championship crown.
Watson won the Masters in April for his first major victory.  Golf’s second major tournament of the year is scheduled for
June 14-17 at the Olympic Club’s Lake Course in San Francisco.
The trio will begin first-round play at 7:33 a.m. local time and
their second round at 1:29 p.m.  Defending champion Rory McIlroy of  Northern Ireland  will
play with England’s Luke Donald and Lee Westwood in a group
featuring the top three players in the Official World Golf
Ranking. Donald holds the No. 1 spot, followed by McIlroy and
Westwood.  To contact the reporter on this story:
